     @64 = ~Netherese Spellblade~
     @65 = ~Long before the Sharn trapped the evil Phaerimm beneath the Anauroch Desert, the Netherese archwizard Karsus devised a plan to temporarily become a deity and defeat the Phaerimm himself- subsequently leading to the fall of Netheril known as Karsus's Folly. Some blame the great archwizard Ioulaum for abandoning Netheril and promting Karsus to take such drastic measures. Before his disappearance, and even the start of the war with the Phaerimm, Ioulaum collaborated with Karsus on the creation of this powerful dagger. It's covered in indecipherable Loross written with Draconic script, the Netherese noble tongue and one of the languages of the City of Shade, Thultanthar. It's rumored that the dagger was a gift for Thultanthar's high mage, known only as Lord Shadow. It was Lord Shadow who experimented with the Plane of Shadow, and shifted his entire city over from the Prime Material Plane mere days before Karsus temporarily destroyed the Weave- and it seems like he took this now shade-touched dagger with him for at least 1700 years, before Thultanthar returned to Faerun. This dagger weighs heavily in your hand and is warm to the touch. Merely having it on your person makes you feel uneasy for some reason. The gem mounted in the hilt seems to have an inner light of some sort, though how it can have such illumination and still be so deathly black at its core, you do not know. It is also unknown which enchantments are original to the spellblade and which are from millennia of residing in the Plane of Shadow and being wielded by powerful Shadovar.

