     @122 = ~Whispering Wind~
     @123 = ~James the Page, a mortal man with a humble origin become traveler of both time and space, is the only one known to have ever possessed this ring. It is said that he received it from elders of the gentle race, whoever those may be, no one seems to agree as it changes with every recount- some swear it was an ancient group of elves, others say titans or dragons, and a few even say it was a gift from the gods themselves. One thing is fairly certain though: James lived an incredible life that puts most bardic tales of bravery and heroism to shame. He sailed on the Wandering Eye with Balduran and battled lycanthropes with a sword of gold that he supposedly stole from a dragon's hoard. Being one of the few survivors to make it back to the mainland, James decided to charter his own ship and sail westward, believing the Father of the Four Winds blessed his explorations. Along the way, he angered Talos with his lack of fear or tribute to the Stormlord, but despite the deity leaving no trace of his vessel, James miraculously made it to uncharted shores. While mapping this new world, he saved the fey Prince of Peace from a black dragon and was subsequently knighted by the Queen of Light. Many historians, however, doubt any of this actually happened- seeing as nothing recorded beyong his youth as a page has been uncovered, and it is even said he never made the rank of squire for reasons unknown. Furthermore, many of the characters involved in the wild tale of Sir James have never been documented, only strengthening the resolve of disbelievers. Possibly all that remains of his adventures is this ring, if it was truly his- all you know for sure is that this band of gold, inscribed with magic runes, possesses incredible power.~
