     @141 = ~The delicate yet sturdy craftsmanship of the elven races allows them to design many beautiful yet utilitarian goods. Among these is elven chain mail, which is so finely wrought that it can be worn under normal clothing without revealing its presence. This particular suit is believed to have been created by a long-forgotten apprentice of the legendary elven armorsmith, Asylferund. While the master sought a way to forge chain mail of the highest enchantments, the student focused on smithing armor more practical for warrior rogues and wizards. By studying the magical robes worn by archmages and the dark suits of leather iconic to the Shadowmasters of Amn, Asylferund's apprentice was able to create a suit of armor able to meet the demands of any misson conceivable. Due to the nature of its enchantment, it can only be worn by those of good alignment.

